1
00:00:04,104 --> 00:00:07,441
Who knew this would ever happen?

2
00:00:08,208 --> 00:00:11,011
Why am I gazing at him as he sleeps?

3
00:00:11,979 --> 00:00:15,249
This puppy-like boy...

4
00:00:15,282 --> 00:00:16,416
Let's go see the stars.

5
00:00:16,450 --> 00:00:17,885
...asked me to go see the stars.

6
00:00:17,918 --> 00:00:21,922
He's been in love with a pretty
childhood friend for years.

7
00:00:21,955 --> 00:00:23,957
I'd only get hurt if I fell in love.

8
00:00:24,291 --> 00:00:26,627
But I couldn't stop myself.

9
00:00:27,527 --> 00:00:32,566
And I found him there,
waiting like a loyal little pup.

10
00:00:32,599 --> 00:00:35,736
It's raining.
We can't see the stars tonight.

11
00:00:36,370 --> 00:00:39,506
How am I supposed to resist?

12
00:00:54,054 --> 00:00:56,156
I think you'll fit in this.

13
00:01:03,997 --> 00:01:05,165
Thanks.

14
00:01:10,571 --> 00:01:13,040
Oh, I'll um...

15
00:01:13,073 --> 00:01:15,008
I'll make you some tea.

16
00:01:19,947 --> 00:01:20,814
Nami.

17
00:01:24,518 --> 00:01:25,452
I love you.

18
00:01:34,494 --> 00:01:35,462
Junnosuke?

19
00:01:40,968 --> 00:01:43,503
And he fell asleep, tired.

20
00:01:44,304 --> 00:01:45,605
So here we are.

21
00:01:49,910 --> 00:01:50,877
"I love you."

22
00:01:51,578 --> 00:01:52,879
That's what he said.

23
00:01:55,015 --> 00:02:00,287
Mr. Oashi said Junnosuke
was in love with somebody else.

24
00:02:00,787 --> 00:02:06,660
But no matter the past,
I'm the one he loves now, right?

25
00:02:14,768 --> 00:02:16,470
Good morning, Junnosuke.

26
00:02:16,803 --> 00:02:18,905
I had to leave for work.

27
00:02:19,339 --> 00:02:22,075
There's rice and miso soup in the pot.

28
00:02:22,376 --> 00:02:23,377
Nami.

29
00:02:30,050 --> 00:02:32,619
Good morning, Nami.
Breakfast was delicious.

30
00:02:33,086 --> 00:02:37,024
My heart is so full this morning.

31
00:02:38,525 --> 00:02:41,662
I used to say being normal and average
beats everything.

32
00:02:42,362 --> 00:02:45,732
But my Tokyo boyfriend
is a hot photographer.

33
00:02:45,966 --> 00:02:50,137
He's a bit of an airhead,
but I can't believe my luck.

34
00:02:50,704 --> 00:02:53,740
What if someday we get married?

35
00:02:56,910 --> 00:02:59,046
Aww... shucks.

36
00:03:04,418 --> 00:03:08,221
You, pledging eternal love
to my little brother?

37
00:03:08,822 --> 00:03:10,457
Never in a million years!

38
00:03:12,492 --> 00:03:13,527
What's wrong?

39
00:03:13,860 --> 00:03:14,795
Were you listening?

40
00:03:14,828 --> 00:03:16,697
I'm sorry, I wasn't.

41
00:03:20,667 --> 00:03:23,637
Pick up two bags
and a bracelet from Celine.

42
00:03:23,670 --> 00:03:27,808
There's no way my boss will accept me
as her brother's girlfriend.

43
00:03:27,841 --> 00:03:29,810
...a present from Nicolai Bergmann.

44
00:03:30,143 --> 00:03:30,911
May I?

45
00:03:31,511 --> 00:03:32,479
Make it quick.

46
00:03:33,080 --> 00:03:37,117
The house journal wants us
to write a feature on Miyavi.

47
00:03:37,150 --> 00:03:38,552
But everybody is too busy.

48
00:03:39,519 --> 00:03:43,390
- What about Izumi?
- That was my thought too.

49
00:03:43,423 --> 00:03:46,293
I'm working on the new
icon bag collection page and...

50
00:03:50,464 --> 00:03:51,898
I'll do it when that's done.

51
00:03:51,932 --> 00:03:52,833
After all that?

52
00:03:54,167 --> 00:03:58,738
She's so capable, everyone
depends on her for so many things.

53
00:03:58,772 --> 00:04:01,141
The polar opposite of
this odd job attendant.

54
00:04:01,808 --> 00:04:06,079
I'd like to promote her
to become an editor by and by.

55
00:04:07,781 --> 00:04:08,982
I agree.

56
00:04:10,117 --> 00:04:13,887
By the way, it's almost time
for our performance review.

57
00:04:13,920 --> 00:04:16,723
Seems like
everybody relies on Ms. Haruka.

58
00:04:18,892 --> 00:04:21,728
Ms. Horai highly values Ms. Haruka.

59
00:04:21,795 --> 00:04:24,831
The same would go for me
if I worked like Ms. Haruka.

60
00:04:25,499 --> 00:04:28,735
Would she accept me
as Junnosuke's girlfriend then?

61
00:04:37,244 --> 00:04:39,813
I'd like to write
the house journal article.

62
00:04:41,214 --> 00:04:42,582
Why you?

63
00:04:42,616 --> 00:04:44,785
You get to write an article, right?

64
00:04:44,818 --> 00:04:46,686
It's creative work!

65
00:04:46,720 --> 00:04:48,722
I'll do my usual tasks too.

66
00:04:50,090 --> 00:04:51,324
What do you say?

67
00:04:54,828 --> 00:04:57,297
Let me do it, please!

68
00:05:02,903 --> 00:05:06,973
Oh My Boss! Love Not Included

69
00:05:07,007 --> 00:05:08,942
Here are the past house journals.

70
00:05:09,209 --> 00:05:12,913
And here are some
from other companies for reference.

71
00:05:13,246 --> 00:05:15,849
I had them ready,
but I won't need them anymore.

72
00:05:16,216 --> 00:05:17,317
Thank you.

73
00:05:18,185 --> 00:05:21,188
You're going to meet
with Rio Hasumi today, right?

74
00:05:21,221 --> 00:05:25,058
I'll send the dress for the interview
to get her size checked.

75
00:05:26,393 --> 00:05:28,061
No, that's okay.

76
00:05:28,595 --> 00:05:30,897
Mr. Handa told us not to overwork you.

77
00:05:30,931 --> 00:05:32,365
I'm totally fine.

78
00:05:32,399 --> 00:05:33,266
Um...

79
00:05:33,833 --> 00:05:35,669
Shall I go instead?

80
00:05:36,036 --> 00:05:38,138
- You?
- Leave it to me.

81
00:05:39,306 --> 00:05:40,840
Okay, thanks.

82
00:05:41,908 --> 00:05:45,912
Take the dress to the stylist
waiting at Anniversaire in Shinagawa.

83
00:05:46,680 --> 00:05:49,583
Hello. What did you want me for?

84
00:05:50,584 --> 00:05:52,752
Our director is on the move.

85
00:05:55,522 --> 00:05:57,724
I thought you should know.

86
00:05:59,192 --> 00:06:03,530
And here. The latest information
on our stockholders.

87
00:06:05,498 --> 00:06:07,934
You're telling me
we're running out of time.

88
00:06:08,802 --> 00:06:11,071
Has Reiko noticed anything?

89
00:06:11,204 --> 00:06:13,506
I don't think so.

90
00:06:13,874 --> 00:06:15,208
Poor Reiko.

91
00:06:15,242 --> 00:06:16,109
Miyavi First Issue Sales

92
00:06:16,109 --> 00:06:19,579
Miyavi is going to be discontinued
no matter how hard she tries.

93
00:06:20,313 --> 00:06:21,414
Right?

94
00:06:21,915 --> 00:06:22,349
Japanese Female Violinist
Wins International Competition

95
00:06:22,349 --> 00:06:24,050
Rio Hasumi.

96
00:06:24,184 --> 00:06:29,789
"Her incredible technique
has won her much fame."

97
00:06:32,058 --> 00:06:34,794
If I write that article
and help with this interview,

98
00:06:34,828 --> 00:06:36,896
Ms. Horai must acknowledge me.

99
00:06:36,930 --> 00:06:39,099
I'm going to be like Ms. Haruka!

100
00:06:42,235 --> 00:06:44,070
Have you left for work?

101
00:06:47,974 --> 00:06:51,111
Yeah. I put the keys in your mailbox.

102
00:06:58,118 --> 00:07:00,120
Watching comedians? Who is it?

103
00:07:00,920 --> 00:07:01,855
Come on.

104
00:07:04,224 --> 00:07:05,992
Did you change shampoo?

105
00:07:06,793 --> 00:07:08,094
You smell different.

106
00:07:12,732 --> 00:07:14,367
We need more bentos over here.

107
00:07:16,036 --> 00:07:17,871
I borrowed your shower.

108
00:07:19,105 --> 00:07:21,508
- Really?
- Should I not have?

109
00:07:23,910 --> 00:07:25,812
It's just kind of embarrassing.

110
00:07:27,013 --> 00:07:28,682
You've seen my room too.

111
00:07:29,949 --> 00:07:30,917
You're right.

112
00:07:31,685 --> 00:07:34,220
I still can't believe it.

113
00:07:35,522 --> 00:07:36,589
Believe what?

114
00:07:40,060 --> 00:07:42,962
That you're my boyfriend.

115
00:07:45,098 --> 00:07:50,170
He IS my boyfriend, right?

116
00:07:50,804 --> 00:07:53,740
He said he loved me,
but he didn't ask me out.

117
00:07:53,773 --> 00:07:57,977
Does that mean
we aren't officially dating yet?

118
00:07:58,812 --> 00:08:02,615
He'll be creeped out if I called him
my boyfriend before asking.

119
00:08:09,222 --> 00:08:12,359
So are we dating?

120
00:08:13,660 --> 00:08:16,062
No, I don't want to ask by texting.

121
00:08:17,097 --> 00:08:19,199
Believe what?

122
00:08:20,400 --> 00:08:21,568
What should I write?

123
00:08:24,003 --> 00:08:26,373
Sorry, I'm going to be late.

124
00:08:26,406 --> 00:08:29,242
The train is delayed.
I'll be about an hour late.

125
00:08:29,275 --> 00:08:30,744
Right, I'm here to work.

126
00:08:32,412 --> 00:08:33,780
I'm getting off!

127
00:08:35,048 --> 00:08:38,752
I'm here to deliver a dress
from Miyavi.

128
00:08:38,785 --> 00:08:40,520
What room is the stylist in?

129
00:08:41,154 --> 00:08:42,789
May I have the name?

130
00:08:42,822 --> 00:08:44,057
Of course, one second.

131
00:08:44,724 --> 00:08:47,527
Mr. Nakazawa told me.

132
00:08:50,530 --> 00:08:53,500
I found them! Thanks, I found them.

133
00:08:53,867 --> 00:08:55,235
Thank you.

134
00:09:09,516 --> 00:09:10,283
Excuse me.

135
00:09:11,151 --> 00:09:12,585
Are you Rio Hasumi?

136
00:09:14,721 --> 00:09:17,424
I'm Suzuki from Miyavi.

137
00:09:17,457 --> 00:09:21,394
Oh, thank you for having me.

138
00:09:21,428 --> 00:09:22,662
Thank you for accepting.

139
00:09:23,396 --> 00:09:27,000
I just had a call from Nakazawa,
the one in charge.

140
00:09:27,667 --> 00:09:30,203
And I'm sorry
but he's going to be a bit late.

141
00:09:30,537 --> 00:09:31,738
Okay.

142
00:09:31,771 --> 00:09:32,806
We're so sorry...

143
00:09:34,641 --> 00:09:36,709
Have you already eaten lunch?

144
00:09:37,744 --> 00:09:38,511
Lunch?

145
00:09:40,547 --> 00:09:43,116
Thanks for joining me.

146
00:09:43,149 --> 00:09:47,287
I've been wanting to come here
ever since I scheduled my return.

147
00:09:47,720 --> 00:09:48,888
I'm surprised.

148
00:09:49,055 --> 00:09:52,759
I thought you might be following
a strict diet or something.

149
00:09:53,259 --> 00:09:55,662
No way. It's not like I'm a model.

150
00:09:56,129 --> 00:09:56,996
Here.

151
00:09:57,464 --> 00:10:00,667
My boss won't eat anything with flour.

152
00:10:00,700 --> 00:10:04,370
I mean, she eats almonds for lunch.

153
00:10:07,307 --> 00:10:08,842
This is so good!

154
00:10:09,876 --> 00:10:13,279
Hey, I have a friend
who has that same bracelet.

155
00:10:13,580 --> 00:10:14,514
It's cute, huh.

156
00:10:15,248 --> 00:10:17,383
Actually, someone gave it to me.

157
00:10:19,018 --> 00:10:19,819
Your boyfriend?

158
00:10:20,420 --> 00:10:23,256
Maybe? I'm not sure.

159
00:10:23,456 --> 00:10:24,424
What?

160
00:10:25,558 --> 00:10:27,994
Well, you see.

161
00:10:28,895 --> 00:10:30,763
He told me he loved me yesterday.

162
00:10:32,132 --> 00:10:36,302
But he hasn't officially asked me out.

163
00:10:36,669 --> 00:10:38,605
So I'm not sure what to call it.

164
00:10:38,738 --> 00:10:41,608
People's feelings change so easily.

165
00:10:41,941 --> 00:10:43,510
You need to make it official.

166
00:10:43,543 --> 00:10:45,645
I know, but...

167
00:10:46,146 --> 00:10:47,614
How do I make him ask me?

168
00:10:47,647 --> 00:10:49,816
I'm so not good at things like that.

169
00:10:50,850 --> 00:10:52,085
No problem.

170
00:10:53,052 --> 00:10:57,390
I'll teach you everything
you need to know.

171
00:10:57,423 --> 00:10:58,491
Really?

172
00:11:01,995 --> 00:11:02,929
Ready.

173
00:11:04,731 --> 00:11:08,601
The reason?
Because I didn't want to regret it.

174
00:11:09,536 --> 00:11:13,606
It took courage to go overseas alone
to try to make it.

175
00:11:13,873 --> 00:11:18,611
But I knew that if I didn't go then,
I might not have another chance.

176
00:11:19,646 --> 00:11:23,149
And I felt then,
that the violin was everything to me.

177
00:11:23,683 --> 00:11:25,785
Could you tell us more about it...

178
00:11:25,818 --> 00:11:29,422
Ms. Rio is so pretty
and down to earth.

179
00:11:29,422 --> 00:11:31,224
She's made her dream come true.

180
00:11:31,724 --> 00:11:33,126
She's so amazing.

181
00:11:36,462 --> 00:11:37,730
- Hey.
- I'm sorry.

182
00:11:38,965 --> 00:11:40,233
Reiko Horai

183
00:11:40,400 --> 00:11:43,970
Oh no! I'm sorry, I have to go back.

184
00:11:44,003 --> 00:11:45,305
Goodbye.

185
00:11:46,739 --> 00:11:49,075
I'm sorry, it's not done yet.
I'll hurry.

186
00:12:00,153 --> 00:12:04,290
What do I do if Junnosuke asks me out?

187
00:12:04,324 --> 00:12:06,292
Will we go on dates every week?

188
00:12:06,693 --> 00:12:07,994
Where to go?

189
00:12:09,529 --> 00:12:10,964
For lunch?

190
00:12:10,997 --> 00:12:13,199
Mr. Ugajin, no actually...

191
00:12:13,566 --> 00:12:16,536
I was wondering what a good place
for a date would be.

192
00:12:17,136 --> 00:12:19,939
Where would you go on a first date?

193
00:12:21,541 --> 00:12:24,410
I couldn't tell you.
I haven't gone on one in a while.

194
00:12:24,444 --> 00:12:27,447
Come on. Just as an example.

195
00:12:28,214 --> 00:12:29,916
How about an aquarium?

196
00:12:29,949 --> 00:12:31,184
Aquarium?

197
00:12:31,217 --> 00:12:34,220
I was given two tickets the other day.

198
00:12:34,253 --> 00:12:36,956
- You can have them.
- Really? Thank you.

199
00:12:38,524 --> 00:12:40,627
I'll drop them off later.

200
00:12:41,361 --> 00:12:42,528
Thank you.

201
00:12:42,962 --> 00:12:43,930
Goodbye.

202
00:12:46,466 --> 00:12:47,934
Any girlfriends?

203
00:12:53,272 --> 00:12:56,175
Where would you go on a first date?

204
00:12:57,243 --> 00:12:58,344
A date...

205
00:12:59,512 --> 00:13:00,446
A date?

206
00:13:04,050 --> 00:13:06,386
Like maybe Reiko?

207
00:13:08,855 --> 00:13:11,758
You know. Dates are nice, aren't they?

208
00:13:13,359 --> 00:13:14,260
Excuse me?

209
00:13:16,496 --> 00:13:17,964
What am I saying, huh?

210
00:13:19,532 --> 00:13:22,235
I'm going out
to have some fish over rice.

211
00:13:24,570 --> 00:13:25,805
Later.

212
00:13:28,107 --> 00:13:30,009
Look after him for me.

213
00:13:41,521 --> 00:13:42,822
Hello, Ms. Horai.

214
00:13:42,889 --> 00:13:44,757
Here's your coffee.

215
00:13:53,366 --> 00:13:54,667
What?

216
00:13:55,535 --> 00:13:58,705
Doesn't your coffee
taste a bit different?

217
00:14:01,307 --> 00:14:04,744
I was at Anniversaire,
so I bought your coffee there.

218
00:14:04,777 --> 00:14:08,414
I was asked to take Rio Hasumi's dress
in place of Ms. Haruka.

219
00:14:08,448 --> 00:14:11,884
So I bought it then.
I'm working on the house journal too.

220
00:14:11,918 --> 00:14:14,620
Oh, and I'll return these
to the reference room.

221
00:14:19,592 --> 00:14:24,163
Junnosuke, I'll make Ms. Horai
acknowledge me!

222
00:14:33,106 --> 00:14:34,674
Do you like crabs?

223
00:14:34,907 --> 00:14:35,675
Crabs?

224
00:14:37,243 --> 00:14:38,010
Crabs?

225
00:14:38,711 --> 00:14:40,813
My mom sent me tons.

226
00:14:42,515 --> 00:14:43,649
You can have some.

227
00:14:45,818 --> 00:14:49,989
This could be my chance
to try what Ms. Rio taught me.

228
00:14:52,725 --> 00:14:54,861
Thanks, I'll pick them up on Saturday.

229
00:14:54,894 --> 00:14:56,062
All right.

230
00:14:56,329 --> 00:14:58,464
I'll make him ask me out.

231
00:15:05,438 --> 00:15:08,975
Mom sends them every year,
but I can't eat it all by myself.

232
00:15:10,276 --> 00:15:11,043
Stay and have some.

233
00:15:11,844 --> 00:15:12,712
Sure.

234
00:15:15,414 --> 00:15:16,682
Commence plan!

235
00:15:17,517 --> 00:15:22,622
Okay, so there are four reasons
a boy won't ask you out.

236
00:15:22,889 --> 00:15:25,291
He's just playing,
he doesn't have confidence,

237
00:15:25,324 --> 00:15:29,128
he thinks you're already dating
because he said he loved you,

238
00:15:29,162 --> 00:15:31,864
or he's just waiting
for the right time to ask.

239
00:15:32,498 --> 00:15:35,668
I'm pretty sure he's not playing me.

240
00:15:35,701 --> 00:15:36,903
Okay.

241
00:15:37,537 --> 00:15:41,040
Then you set up a situation
that makes it easy for him to ask.

242
00:15:45,011 --> 00:15:47,613
Do you cook for yourself a lot?

243
00:15:47,647 --> 00:15:49,582
Just sometimes.

244
00:15:49,882 --> 00:15:51,017
I mostly eat out.

245
00:15:52,318 --> 00:15:57,857
I've always wanted to make beef stew
for my boyfriend when I got one.

246
00:15:58,124 --> 00:16:03,462
If he's just not confident, he'll say,
"I hope you will for me someday."

247
00:16:03,496 --> 00:16:06,933
If he already thinks you're dating,
he'll ask you to make it.

248
00:16:07,533 --> 00:16:08,968
Easy as that.

249
00:16:09,669 --> 00:16:15,007
If he's just waiting for a chance
to ask you out, he will right there.

250
00:16:15,741 --> 00:16:17,443
Beef stew, huh?

251
00:16:19,178 --> 00:16:19,812
I...

252
00:16:20,713 --> 00:16:22,949
Come on, which is it?

253
00:16:23,916 --> 00:16:26,219
I like pouring stew over rice.

254
00:16:26,485 --> 00:16:28,421
Some don't, you know?

255
00:16:29,422 --> 00:16:33,059
Which is this? Is he being evasive?

256
00:16:33,392 --> 00:16:35,761
How about you?

257
00:16:36,229 --> 00:16:38,764
I guess not.

258
00:16:38,965 --> 00:16:42,969
Big mistake.
Don't mention food to Junnosuke.

259
00:16:43,469 --> 00:16:44,503
Next step.

260
00:16:45,304 --> 00:16:50,610
Talk about your relationship,
starting from when you met.

261
00:16:51,210 --> 00:16:55,081
That way, you'll naturally
start to talk about the future.

262
00:16:55,648 --> 00:17:00,019
So ask him how he feels
about your relationship.

263
00:17:01,520 --> 00:17:05,057
Come to think of it,
we first met at that bench, huh?

264
00:17:06,826 --> 00:17:08,394
Almost three months ago now.

265
00:17:12,431 --> 00:17:17,670
And now, we want to see each other,
so we do.

266
00:17:19,138 --> 00:17:20,339
I wonder what this is.

267
00:17:22,875 --> 00:17:25,711
Which is it?
Are we dating? Or do you want to date?

268
00:17:27,313 --> 00:17:28,881
It's a fun relationship.

269
00:17:29,849 --> 00:17:34,220
You know,
like cooking meat with pineapples.

270
00:17:34,487 --> 00:17:36,022
No, I don't.

271
00:17:36,055 --> 00:17:39,792
If you still can't figure it out...

272
00:17:40,493 --> 00:17:41,794
Yes?

273
00:17:42,228 --> 00:17:43,596
He's an airhead.

274
00:17:43,629 --> 00:17:45,698
That's actually very probable.

275
00:17:45,731 --> 00:17:48,567
Then you'll just have to come out
and say it.

276
00:17:49,936 --> 00:17:50,736
Junnosuke.

277
00:17:52,805 --> 00:17:53,639
Look.

278
00:17:55,374 --> 00:17:57,143
I want to hear it in words.

279
00:17:59,312 --> 00:18:02,949
You said you loved me the other day.

280
00:18:05,384 --> 00:18:07,053
I was so happy.

281
00:18:07,920 --> 00:18:10,756
So I want to continue seeing you.

282
00:18:10,790 --> 00:18:14,427
And go out to eat
and go places with you.

283
00:18:17,029 --> 00:18:18,030
So...

284
00:18:18,831 --> 00:18:22,268
I hope we can clarify that
this is that kind of relationship.

285
00:18:24,704 --> 00:18:26,572
Right, in words.

286
00:18:28,140 --> 00:18:28,908
Okay.

287
00:18:30,176 --> 00:18:31,877
He finally understood.

288
00:18:33,846 --> 00:18:35,948
- Nami.
- Yes.

289
00:18:42,154 --> 00:18:43,055
Will you...

290
00:18:47,860 --> 00:18:49,095
Will you...

291
00:18:54,233 --> 00:18:55,101
One second.

292
00:18:57,036 --> 00:18:59,038
We were so close!

293
00:19:00,606 --> 00:19:01,374
Sis?

294
00:19:03,376 --> 00:19:04,176
Is someone coming?

295
00:19:04,210 --> 00:19:05,044
Why?

296
00:19:05,077 --> 00:19:07,246
I have to finish this
so I can go to Junnosuke.

297
00:19:07,279 --> 00:19:08,714
You can't handle both.

298
00:19:08,748 --> 00:19:10,683
Heads will roll, and not just ours.

299
00:19:10,716 --> 00:19:12,351
I can't believe what I've done.

300
00:19:12,385 --> 00:19:15,021
It's so wonderful
being in love at that stage.

301
00:19:15,054 --> 00:19:17,890
That's how you climb up,
one step at a time.

302
00:19:24,463 --> 00:19:25,631
Why is she here?

303
00:19:29,502 --> 00:19:30,269
What is it?

304
00:19:30,603 --> 00:19:32,471
You told me to come get a crab.

305
00:19:35,474 --> 00:19:38,077
- I did!
- Why now?

306
00:19:38,110 --> 00:19:39,345
Hurry up and open it.

307
00:19:43,149 --> 00:19:44,283
Okay, sure.

308
00:19:47,586 --> 00:19:50,690
How am I supposed to explain
why I'm here?

309
00:19:51,624 --> 00:19:53,125
I'll leave the crab outside.

310
00:19:53,159 --> 00:19:54,760
No, that's just weird.

311
00:19:54,794 --> 00:19:58,697
I'm going home!
I'll run down the stairs.

312
00:19:58,998 --> 00:19:59,865
Bye!

313
00:20:09,508 --> 00:20:10,476
She's here.

314
00:20:11,210 --> 00:20:12,912
Where can I hide?

315
00:20:12,945 --> 00:20:14,547
The closet in that room!

316
00:20:15,881 --> 00:20:16,816
Coming.

317
00:20:18,717 --> 00:20:19,485
I forgot!

318
00:20:20,486 --> 00:20:21,821
- The crab?
- My shoes.

319
00:20:25,825 --> 00:20:26,792
Here you go.

320
00:20:29,395 --> 00:20:30,830
Don't you have like a box?

321
00:20:31,397 --> 00:20:32,231
You're right.

322
00:20:41,307 --> 00:20:42,374
You're boiling some?

323
00:20:45,945 --> 00:20:47,146
What?

324
00:20:47,713 --> 00:20:48,948
Nothing.

325
00:20:56,322 --> 00:20:57,323
Is someone coming?

326
00:20:58,724 --> 00:20:59,658
No, why?

327
00:21:05,698 --> 00:21:07,366
That's um...

328
00:21:10,536 --> 00:21:13,506
Mom came the other day.
She bought a copy of Miyavi.

329
00:21:13,706 --> 00:21:14,473
Really.

330
00:21:15,141 --> 00:21:18,310
So, did you introduce her
to your fake girlfriend?

331
00:21:21,647 --> 00:21:22,481
Just kidding.

332
00:21:23,315 --> 00:21:25,084
I know you hate matchmaking.

333
00:21:27,686 --> 00:21:30,556
But you'll still succeed
Horai Paperworks, right?

334
00:21:32,558 --> 00:21:33,359
Yeah.

335
00:21:33,792 --> 00:21:35,261
Horai Paperworks?

336
00:21:42,168 --> 00:21:43,669
Horai Paperworks

337
00:21:43,702 --> 00:21:44,503
Seriously?

338
00:21:44,537 --> 00:21:45,671
Ouch...

339
00:22:01,253 --> 00:22:02,354
Hello.

340
00:22:08,260 --> 00:22:09,028
I'm telling her.

341
00:22:10,663 --> 00:22:12,965
Sis, I...

342
00:22:13,666 --> 00:22:14,366
What?

343
00:22:14,667 --> 00:22:15,701
I...

344
00:22:17,369 --> 00:22:18,504
I love...

345
00:22:22,641 --> 00:22:23,409
...crabs.

346
00:22:24,510 --> 00:22:27,313
I came over because I wanted some.

347
00:22:27,346 --> 00:22:32,418
I became friends with Junnosuke
only because I wanted some crabs.

348
00:22:33,752 --> 00:22:38,123
If she finds out now, she'll be like,
"You can't even manage your job."

349
00:22:38,157 --> 00:22:41,360
She'll try to stop us.
So please understand, Junnosuke!

350
00:22:43,262 --> 00:22:44,296
You did?

351
00:22:45,431 --> 00:22:46,632
Yeah...

352
00:22:48,100 --> 00:22:49,268
Just for the crabs...

353
00:22:49,668 --> 00:22:51,003
You understand, don't you?

354
00:22:53,339 --> 00:22:54,673
It was for the crabs, huh.

355
00:22:55,674 --> 00:22:56,675
You believed that?

356
00:23:02,381 --> 00:23:03,449
Good morning.

357
00:23:06,318 --> 00:23:07,253
Ms. Horai.

358
00:23:08,587 --> 00:23:10,589
I'm in love with Junnosuke.

359
00:23:12,057 --> 00:23:14,093
You might not consent yet.

360
00:23:14,960 --> 00:23:18,197
But I'll work hard and do my best
until you do.

361
00:23:25,337 --> 00:23:30,976
You and Junnosuke can date whomever
you want. It's none of my business.

362
00:23:31,744 --> 00:23:34,980
But if you let it get to your head
and affect your work,

363
00:23:36,015 --> 00:23:37,049
you might as well quit now.

364
00:23:38,017 --> 00:23:39,585
But...

365
00:23:40,419 --> 00:23:42,955
You tell me to quit every two words.

366
00:23:44,056 --> 00:23:47,993
People fall in love and get married
while maintaining a job all the time.

367
00:23:48,027 --> 00:23:50,195
Why do I have to choose
one or the other?

368
00:23:51,463 --> 00:23:52,464
Look.

369
00:23:53,933 --> 00:23:55,801
You really think you can handle both?

370
00:23:57,469 --> 00:23:58,604
I can.

371
00:23:58,904 --> 00:24:00,072
I will.

372
00:24:05,144 --> 00:24:07,112
Japan International Photo Awards

373
00:24:21,160 --> 00:24:25,497
I want to concentrate on the violin.
I can't let it end as just a dream.

374
00:24:26,198 --> 00:24:28,200
I want to make it come true.

375
00:24:42,514 --> 00:24:45,017
I have to finish this
so I can go to Junnosuke.

376
00:24:45,617 --> 00:24:47,486
Don't waste time, make time.

377
00:24:49,421 --> 00:24:52,691
I shouldn't have to sacrifice
my personal life for work.

378
00:24:53,559 --> 00:24:58,230
I wonder how all the other women
make them both work.

379
00:24:58,530 --> 00:25:00,366
Humans are greedy creatures.

380
00:25:00,399 --> 00:25:01,700
Mr. Handa.

381
00:25:02,134 --> 00:25:04,203
You get one, you'll want another.

382
00:25:04,937 --> 00:25:08,340
But there's only so much
one can handle.

383
00:25:08,607 --> 00:25:11,210
So you have to choose
what you want for yourself.

384
00:25:12,344 --> 00:25:15,280
Either that,
or find a way to handle both.

385
00:25:20,486 --> 00:25:22,488
Find a way to handle both?

386
00:25:24,623 --> 00:25:25,457
There you are.

387
00:25:25,724 --> 00:25:28,660
You delivered Rio Hasumi's dress,
didn't you?

388
00:25:29,261 --> 00:25:31,230
- Yes.
- The stylist called.

389
00:25:31,263 --> 00:25:33,932
He said he hasn't gotten it yet.

390
00:25:33,966 --> 00:25:35,334
But I delivered it.

391
00:25:35,367 --> 00:25:36,468
What was his name?

392
00:25:36,869 --> 00:25:38,036
He was a guy, right?

393
00:25:38,303 --> 00:25:39,638
Did you make sure?

394
00:25:40,739 --> 00:25:44,076
Excuse me, one second!

395
00:25:44,109 --> 00:25:46,145
This is from the editing department.

396
00:25:46,478 --> 00:25:47,546
Editing department?

397
00:25:52,684 --> 00:25:56,688
The interlocutor designed it
especially for Rio Hasumi.

398
00:25:57,389 --> 00:26:01,093
If we lose it, heads will roll,
and not just ours.

399
00:26:08,667 --> 00:26:13,305
Excuse me, have there been
any interviews by magazines held here?

400
00:26:13,772 --> 00:26:17,643
On the same day as Miyavi.
There had to have been one.

401
00:26:17,676 --> 00:26:20,612
I'm sorry, but I can't give out
such information.

402
00:26:20,646 --> 00:26:24,249
I may have accidentally handed them
a really important dress.

403
00:26:24,283 --> 00:26:28,654
Shall I contact them for you and ask?

404
00:26:28,687 --> 00:26:29,455
Please!

405
00:26:31,723 --> 00:26:33,158
It serves me right.

406
00:26:33,525 --> 00:26:36,094
I'd let this thing with Junnosuke
affect my work.

407
00:26:40,699 --> 00:26:41,633
Hello?

408
00:26:42,468 --> 00:26:45,337
You're Reiko's assistant girl.

409
00:26:46,605 --> 00:26:49,475
It's me. Editor-in-chief of Zeal.

410
00:26:49,508 --> 00:26:51,009
Asami Takahashi.

411
00:26:52,110 --> 00:26:55,314
I got a call from the hotel
about some dress mixup.

412
00:26:56,782 --> 00:26:58,817
You have it?

413
00:26:58,851 --> 00:27:01,286
Who knows?
I don't look after such things.

414
00:27:01,320 --> 00:27:06,592
What a dummy, handing an important
dress to the rival's stylist.

415
00:27:06,625 --> 00:27:10,062
Can you tell me where it is
so I can look for it?

416
00:27:10,496 --> 00:27:12,764
And why would I do that?

417
00:27:13,031 --> 00:27:14,132
Well...

418
00:27:17,736 --> 00:27:19,771
They're shooting at Sogetsu Hall.

419
00:27:20,239 --> 00:27:21,039
Now?

420
00:27:22,174 --> 00:27:24,142
Be sure you put them back.

421
00:27:24,176 --> 00:27:25,611
- Thank you.
- We're so sorry.

422
00:27:25,644 --> 00:27:26,445
Excuse us.

423
00:27:27,846 --> 00:27:29,615
I'm sorry for troubling you.

424
00:27:29,882 --> 00:27:31,049
Later, just hurry.

425
00:27:32,951 --> 00:27:35,120
- A yellow dress, right?
- Yes.

426
00:27:37,990 --> 00:27:38,857
Is this it?

427
00:27:38,891 --> 00:27:39,892
No, not that.

428
00:27:43,161 --> 00:27:43,929
She's ready.

429
00:27:47,332 --> 00:27:48,200
There it is!

430
00:27:54,540 --> 00:27:58,443
- That dress!
- Here she is, Ms. Momiji Yamamura!

431
00:27:58,777 --> 00:28:01,213
Hello, thank you.

432
00:28:02,714 --> 00:28:05,751
Isn't it pretty?
I just love this dress.

433
00:28:06,418 --> 00:28:07,452
Oh no...

434
00:28:07,753 --> 00:28:11,290
We can't let that dress
be published in a different magazine.

435
00:28:11,723 --> 00:28:13,191
- I'll ask her.
- Impossible.

436
00:28:13,225 --> 00:28:15,060
- I will.
- Hey!

437
00:28:15,694 --> 00:28:16,695
Excuse me.

438
00:28:17,429 --> 00:28:20,766
That dress... there was a mixup.

439
00:28:21,099 --> 00:28:23,468
Won't you please change into
something else?

440
00:28:24,069 --> 00:28:25,337
Who are you?

441
00:28:25,370 --> 00:28:26,805
I'm very sorry.

442
00:28:27,306 --> 00:28:29,141
Why should I?

443
00:28:29,675 --> 00:28:32,644
- Somebody!
- Please stand back.

444
00:28:32,678 --> 00:28:34,713
We need that dress...

445
00:28:39,351 --> 00:28:41,553
There was a mixup, it was my mistake.

446
00:28:44,323 --> 00:28:46,191
It's not supposed to be...

447
00:28:52,531 --> 00:28:54,066
It's been a while, Ms. Momiji.

448
00:28:56,969 --> 00:28:58,637
Why hello, Reiko!

449
00:28:58,670 --> 00:29:00,906
I just thought I'd drop by.

450
00:29:01,173 --> 00:29:05,644
Here is the dress by Tomari Togo
that you said you wanted to wear.

451
00:29:06,612 --> 00:29:10,015
I had him make it
with "momiji" patterns like your name.

452
00:29:10,048 --> 00:29:12,084
My, how beautiful.

453
00:29:13,719 --> 00:29:15,621
Is this why you asked me to change?

454
00:29:16,955 --> 00:29:19,157
You should've just said so.

455
00:29:20,459 --> 00:29:22,828
What do you think? Do I look nice?

456
00:29:22,861 --> 00:29:24,496
You look perfect.

457
00:29:29,167 --> 00:29:30,268
Ms. Horai.

458
00:29:33,505 --> 00:29:35,007
I'm so sorry.

459
00:29:36,274 --> 00:29:38,043
For all the trouble I caused.

460
00:29:40,612 --> 00:29:43,281
Do you understand now
why Izumi is so dependable?

461
00:29:46,451 --> 00:29:49,221
She doesn't work half-heartedly
like you do.

462
00:30:13,945 --> 00:30:15,580
I can't believe what I've done.

463
00:30:16,448 --> 00:30:18,483
I said I'd manage both.

464
00:30:19,084 --> 00:30:21,019
And caused everyone so much trouble.

465
00:30:24,089 --> 00:30:25,090
Hello.

466
00:30:31,229 --> 00:30:32,097
Um...

467
00:30:32,831 --> 00:30:36,802
It's for the house journal.
But I don't know how to fix it.

468
00:30:37,569 --> 00:30:39,404
It's beyond fixing.

469
00:30:39,838 --> 00:30:41,673
Rambles on about nothing.

470
00:30:41,873 --> 00:30:43,241
Did you even cover for this?

471
00:30:43,275 --> 00:30:44,042
No...

472
00:30:44,309 --> 00:30:48,113
It's about Miyavi,
and I'm part of the team too.

473
00:30:48,146 --> 00:30:51,683
The whole company
already knows what you know.

474
00:30:54,786 --> 00:30:58,123
People read because they want to know
what they already don't.

475
00:30:59,858 --> 00:31:00,759
Bye.

476
00:31:02,928 --> 00:31:03,929
Goodbye.

477
00:31:07,966 --> 00:31:08,834
She's right.

478
00:31:16,141 --> 00:31:16,274
Survey

479
00:31:16,274 --> 00:31:17,075
Please.

480
00:31:17,843 --> 00:31:18,910
Please.

481
00:31:19,644 --> 00:31:20,645
Please.

482
00:31:21,279 --> 00:31:22,447
Please.

483
00:31:23,915 --> 00:31:25,183
What's this, a survey?

484
00:31:25,350 --> 00:31:26,418
For the house journal.

485
00:31:26,451 --> 00:31:28,186
Here's the proposals she rejected.

486
00:31:28,220 --> 00:31:29,121
But what for?

487
00:31:29,154 --> 00:31:30,255
Thank you.

488
00:31:30,288 --> 00:31:33,191
Ms. Yui, can I ask you some questions?

489
00:31:33,225 --> 00:31:34,326
I have an interview.

490
00:31:34,359 --> 00:31:36,428
We can talk as you walk.

491
00:31:46,471 --> 00:31:47,239
Still here?

492
00:31:48,206 --> 00:31:50,275
The house journal is due tomorrow.

493
00:31:50,776 --> 00:31:52,477
Why are you here so late?

494
00:31:54,679 --> 00:31:57,649
I want to prepare
for my next interview.

495
00:32:01,887 --> 00:32:06,291
Could you show me how to make a graph
on the computer?

496
00:32:06,558 --> 00:32:07,559
A graph?

497
00:32:10,462 --> 00:32:12,597
- You can't even do that?
- Thank you.

498
00:32:14,232 --> 00:32:15,233
Move.

499
00:32:15,267 --> 00:32:16,034
Sorry.

500
00:32:19,638 --> 00:32:20,672
For the survey, huh.

501
00:32:22,007 --> 00:32:27,712
This editing work.
It's all taking surveys and stuff.

502
00:32:27,746 --> 00:32:30,315
And asking for comments
and writing them up.

503
00:32:30,348 --> 00:32:32,150
It's pretty tedious, huh.

504
00:32:33,652 --> 00:32:35,520
And that's what's important.

505
00:32:36,454 --> 00:32:37,355
What is?

506
00:32:37,989 --> 00:32:41,993
People say magazine editing
is a creative job.

507
00:32:42,027 --> 00:32:46,031
But behind the showy facade,
most of it is clerical work.

508
00:32:46,698 --> 00:32:47,732
Clerical work?

509
00:32:47,966 --> 00:32:51,736
Like, when you do an interview.

510
00:32:52,637 --> 00:32:58,376
You contact the model and the staff,
schedule interviews, negotiate fees.

511
00:32:58,844 --> 00:33:01,713
Book the location or studio
or whatever.

512
00:33:01,746 --> 00:33:03,748
All that clerical stuff.

513
00:33:07,619 --> 00:33:09,020
Have you seen "The Karate Kid"?

514
00:33:09,621 --> 00:33:10,522
No.

515
00:33:12,190 --> 00:33:16,027
This boy Daniel
trains under a karate master.

516
00:33:16,628 --> 00:33:22,334
But he makes Daniel do odd jobs like
waxing floors and painting fences.

517
00:33:23,368 --> 00:33:28,440
And Daniel gets mad and asks
the master to teach him karate.

518
00:33:28,473 --> 00:33:32,277
But actually, all those odd jobs
he was made to do

519
00:33:32,310 --> 00:33:34,613
were fundamental karate moves.

520
00:33:34,913 --> 00:33:39,417
So Daniel had mastered the essence
of karate through odd jobs.

521
00:33:40,752 --> 00:33:42,287
So, yeah.

522
00:33:45,056 --> 00:33:49,427
The essence of the job
is in the tedious tasks people hate.

523
00:33:50,462 --> 00:33:54,132
The essence of the work
is in the odd jobs.

524
00:33:55,634 --> 00:33:56,601
There, done.

525
00:33:57,435 --> 00:33:58,470
Wow!

526
00:33:58,503 --> 00:34:00,005
It's nothing.

527
00:34:01,907 --> 00:34:05,076
Guess I'll get to work too.

528
00:34:05,110 --> 00:34:06,544
Thank you.

529
00:34:12,150 --> 00:34:13,818
All right.

530
00:34:18,189 --> 00:34:19,524
Can you come out for a minute?

531
00:34:25,397 --> 00:34:26,164
I'm sorry

532
00:34:26,164 --> 00:34:27,699
I'll be at our bench.

533
00:34:34,272 --> 00:34:35,273
Just one minute.

534
00:34:37,442 --> 00:34:38,610
Junnosuke!

535
00:34:39,744 --> 00:34:40,779
What is it?

536
00:34:42,314 --> 00:34:43,081
Here.

537
00:34:43,648 --> 00:34:45,750
Crab rice balls and crab miso soup.

538
00:34:48,286 --> 00:34:49,721
You made it for me?

539
00:34:50,088 --> 00:34:52,057
- Yeah.
- Really?

540
00:34:52,490 --> 00:34:54,392
Gosh, I'm so happy.

541
00:34:55,093 --> 00:34:56,728
Hope it gets you through.

542
00:34:58,330 --> 00:34:59,631
Thank you.

543
00:35:01,099 --> 00:35:02,500
I don't want to bother you, so.

544
00:35:05,570 --> 00:35:06,338
Bye.

545
00:35:07,605 --> 00:35:08,406
Bye.

546
00:35:23,822 --> 00:35:24,689
Nami.

547
00:35:25,757 --> 00:35:26,625
Yes?

548
00:35:40,505 --> 00:35:41,706
Recharging.

549
00:35:50,615 --> 00:35:52,650
I feel stronger now.

550
00:35:54,786 --> 00:35:55,620
Me too.

551
00:36:12,937 --> 00:36:14,606
Thank you for this food.

552
00:36:19,110 --> 00:36:21,312
I know Ms. Horai thinks differently.

553
00:36:21,679 --> 00:36:25,016
But our personal lives
can help us get through work too.

554
00:37:00,719 --> 00:37:03,088
Miyavi Staff Members

555
00:37:04,889 --> 00:37:07,025
Timeline up to Miyavi's First Issue

556
00:37:07,192 --> 00:37:07,859
All About Reiko Horai

557
00:37:15,800 --> 00:37:16,734
I did it.

558
00:37:20,271 --> 00:37:23,942
I really did it.

559
00:37:28,046 --> 00:37:28,813
Hey.

560
00:37:56,574 --> 00:37:58,543
All About Reiko Horai

561
00:38:15,226 --> 00:38:17,328
Is "sketch" a fashion term?

562
00:38:18,997 --> 00:38:19,764
Ouch.

563
00:38:19,964 --> 00:38:23,902
How the editor feels
really affects how the pages end up.

564
00:38:28,173 --> 00:38:28,940
My boyfriend.

565
00:38:29,274 --> 00:38:30,041
Hello.

566
00:38:30,441 --> 00:38:31,576
I'll wait at our bench.

567
00:38:33,278 --> 00:38:35,413
Going to see the stars?

568
00:39:19,924 --> 00:39:21,459
What were you thinking?

569
00:39:22,493 --> 00:39:23,895
Is it bad?

570
00:39:24,195 --> 00:39:27,432
"Proposals Rejected
by Editor-in-Chief Reiko Horai"?

571
00:39:27,465 --> 00:39:30,301
"Reiko Horai's Killer Phrases"?

572
00:39:30,335 --> 00:39:32,737
"How to Dress Like Reiko Horai"?

573
00:39:33,037 --> 00:39:35,173
You thought I'd okay this?

574
00:39:36,374 --> 00:39:38,543
I thought everybody
would be interested.

575
00:39:40,678 --> 00:39:41,813
I'm sorry.

576
00:39:53,829 --> 00:39:55,864
It didn't work out, huh?

577
00:39:58,800 --> 00:40:00,769
But I gave it my best.

578
00:40:01,937 --> 00:40:04,206
So I'm actually not feeling so bad.

579
00:40:04,739 --> 00:40:07,642
You have a new view now, huh?

580
00:40:08,477 --> 00:40:09,811
A new view?

581
00:40:10,178 --> 00:40:11,847
No matter the result,

582
00:40:11,880 --> 00:40:16,818
if you gave it your best,
you'll see where to aim next.

583
00:40:17,185 --> 00:40:19,354
You see things
you didn't see yesterday.

584
00:40:20,222 --> 00:40:22,958
That's how you climb up,
one step at a time.

585
00:40:24,192 --> 00:40:25,193
The next step, huh.

586
00:40:26,862 --> 00:40:28,663
Shoot, I have to order flowers.

587
00:40:29,231 --> 00:40:32,534
I'm helping out with an interview
tomorrow at Anniversaire.

588
00:40:32,567 --> 00:40:33,468
Later!

589
00:40:34,469 --> 00:40:35,337
Good luck.

590
00:40:42,177 --> 00:40:42,844
Proposals Rejected
by Editor-in-Chief Reiko Horai

591
00:40:42,844 --> 00:40:44,045
Oh my...

592
00:40:47,182 --> 00:40:50,719
Fix it and hand it to
the house journal editors.

593
00:40:50,919 --> 00:40:52,020
Of course.

594
00:40:56,191 --> 00:40:57,292
Quite interesting.

595
00:40:57,325 --> 00:40:59,461
I'll take you to a party

596
00:40:59,494 --> 00:41:01,830
You may speak
only when I ask you a question

597
00:41:04,900 --> 00:41:05,734
Excuse me.

598
00:41:11,673 --> 00:41:12,774
Hello.

599
00:41:13,542 --> 00:41:15,410
- May I?
- Yes.

600
00:41:16,244 --> 00:41:17,546
Where's Ms. Suzuki?

601
00:41:17,579 --> 00:41:19,047
She's not in now.

602
00:41:20,749 --> 00:41:23,385
These are tickets to the aquarium.

603
00:41:24,085 --> 00:41:25,887
- For a date...
- A date?

604
00:41:28,056 --> 00:41:30,158
You and Suzuki?

605
00:41:31,560 --> 00:41:32,494
No.

606
00:41:33,795 --> 00:41:36,798
There's no way she and I
would go on a date.

607
00:41:40,168 --> 00:41:42,404
Of course, forgive me.

608
00:41:43,738 --> 00:41:46,775
So that date...

609
00:41:46,808 --> 00:41:47,842
Is it with me?

610
00:41:51,046 --> 00:41:54,182
Wait, I'm not prepared...

611
00:41:54,349 --> 00:41:57,619
I have to focus on work.
I have lots of responsibilities...

612
00:41:57,652 --> 00:41:59,120
You're getting me wrong.

613
00:42:01,523 --> 00:42:03,358
Because, look.

614
00:42:03,758 --> 00:42:06,561
I'm too old for you, aren't I?

615
00:42:07,329 --> 00:42:09,231
- You're young...
- No, you aren't.

616
00:42:11,533 --> 00:42:12,834
I...

617
00:42:13,969 --> 00:42:17,839
You are not too old for me.

618
00:42:25,313 --> 00:42:26,114
Okay.

619
00:42:27,215 --> 00:42:28,149
Let's go then.

620
00:42:30,518 --> 00:42:31,419
Yes.

621
00:42:32,454 --> 00:42:35,824
Lastly, what do dreams mean to you?

622
00:42:36,458 --> 00:42:38,059
Dreams?

623
00:42:38,994 --> 00:42:42,397
Once you make up your mind,
your dream turns into a goal.

624
00:42:43,131 --> 00:42:45,967
I didn't want it to end as a dream.

625
00:42:46,001 --> 00:42:47,802
And chose to leave Japan.

626
00:42:48,837 --> 00:42:53,975
I'm really grateful for myself
that I made that decision.

627
00:42:55,944 --> 00:42:57,712
Thank you so much.

628
00:42:57,746 --> 00:43:00,815
We'll take your photographs now,
and that will be all.

629
00:43:01,383 --> 00:43:02,217
Thank you.

630
00:43:02,250 --> 00:43:04,286
Thank you.

631
00:43:07,656 --> 00:43:08,423
Hey.

632
00:43:09,391 --> 00:43:10,759
So how was it?

633
00:43:12,527 --> 00:43:13,895
It was chaos.

634
00:43:14,162 --> 00:43:16,698
His sister suddenly came, and...

635
00:43:16,898 --> 00:43:19,567
Then I got busy with work.

636
00:43:19,601 --> 00:43:23,171
Yeah. But it's so wonderful
being in love at that stage.

637
00:43:23,204 --> 00:43:25,307
Lucky you!

638
00:43:27,075 --> 00:43:30,011
Do you have a boyfriend?

639
00:43:30,545 --> 00:43:31,413
Nope.

640
00:43:31,880 --> 00:43:34,149
I've given my all to the violin.

641
00:43:35,684 --> 00:43:39,521
There was a guy
I really loved a long time ago.

642
00:43:40,255 --> 00:43:41,122
Really?

643
00:43:42,357 --> 00:43:43,992
Ms. Rio, we're ready.

644
00:43:46,428 --> 00:43:47,896
We'll talk later.

645
00:43:49,497 --> 00:43:50,565
I'm ready.

646
00:43:50,598 --> 00:43:52,200
Take a seat here please.

647
00:43:52,233 --> 00:43:55,070
Okay, we're done.

648
00:43:55,537 --> 00:43:58,606
You're on your phone a lot these days.

649
00:43:58,640 --> 00:44:00,742
Did you get a girlfriend or something?

650
00:44:01,309 --> 00:44:02,277
Not saying.

651
00:44:03,178 --> 00:44:05,613
Seriously? You got a girlfriend?

652
00:44:07,449 --> 00:44:09,484
No way, really?

653
00:44:09,517 --> 00:44:11,720
You're basically saying yes.

654
00:44:11,753 --> 00:44:12,854
You mean it?

655
00:44:14,189 --> 00:44:16,057
It's not Haruka, is it?

656
00:44:16,658 --> 00:44:17,659
Of course not.

657
00:44:21,162 --> 00:44:22,664
Nami? Seriously?

658
00:44:25,100 --> 00:44:27,335
Who asked who out?

659
00:44:27,769 --> 00:44:28,536
Ask out?

660
00:44:28,903 --> 00:44:30,338
Yeah, who said it?

661
00:44:31,339 --> 00:44:34,175
Neither of us have, I don't think.

662
00:44:36,611 --> 00:44:37,712
You haven't?

663
00:44:38,947 --> 00:44:40,281
Should I?

664
00:44:40,815 --> 00:44:44,185
I'm sure all girls
would rather be asked.

665
00:44:44,786 --> 00:44:46,888
Nami isn't like that...

666
00:44:47,255 --> 00:44:51,559
I've always wanted to make beef stew
for my boyfriend when I got one.

667
00:44:51,593 --> 00:44:55,163
I want to hear it in words.

668
00:45:00,201 --> 00:45:01,336
I gotta go.

669
00:45:02,237 --> 00:45:04,272
Huh? Mr. Jun?

670
00:45:05,039 --> 00:45:06,908
You're going to ask her out?

671
00:45:07,542 --> 00:45:11,312
Dang, you go man.

672
00:45:44,913 --> 00:45:45,947
Nami!

673
00:45:48,716 --> 00:45:49,717
Why are you here?

674
00:45:50,618 --> 00:45:52,554
You said you'd be here today.

675
00:45:53,822 --> 00:45:55,623
I wanted to tell you something.

676
00:45:58,893 --> 00:46:00,028
I...

677
00:46:00,628 --> 00:46:01,963
You know him?

678
00:46:11,940 --> 00:46:15,009
Yeah, he's actually...

679
00:46:23,451 --> 00:46:24,552
Why are you here?

680
00:46:26,020 --> 00:46:28,089
You know Ms. Rio?

681
00:46:28,957 --> 00:46:29,924
What a coincidence.

682
00:46:32,360 --> 00:46:34,496
We're childhood friends.

683
00:46:35,130 --> 00:46:36,331
Childhood friends?

684
00:46:37,065 --> 00:46:41,703
He's been in love with a pretty
childhood friend for years.

685
00:46:42,136 --> 00:46:45,874
There was a guy
I really loved a long time ago.

686
00:46:47,809 --> 00:46:52,847
The person Junnosuke had loved
all those years...

687
00:46:54,115 --> 00:46:56,351
Long time no see, Jun.

688
00:46:58,052 --> 00:46:58,853
Yeah...

689
00:47:17,472 --> 00:47:17,705
Issue number two.

690
00:47:17,705 --> 00:47:18,573
Next episode

691
00:47:18,573 --> 00:47:19,707
Want to be an assistant?

692
00:47:19,741 --> 00:47:22,343
Why not? You won't have to do
odd jobs for the time being.

693
00:47:22,377 --> 00:47:23,111
Am I unwelcome?

694
00:47:23,144 --> 00:47:24,679
Why are you and Nami together?

695
00:47:24,712 --> 00:47:26,147
This is pandemonium.

696
00:47:26,181 --> 00:47:29,217
It's not me that Junnosuke loves.

697
00:47:29,217 --> 00:47:29,551
This drama is fictional

698
00:47:29,551 --> 00:47:32,220
I'd never make you cry.
